Slide 12 — Experiment 02 Config

"Experiment 02 keeps everything else identical to Exp 01 — same optimizer, same LR, same schedule — and changes only the loss functions.


We switch from Cross Entropy to Focal Loss with α=0.25 and γ=2.0. These are the values from the original RetinaNet paper, well-validated for class imbalance. Focal Loss down-weights easy negatives — all that background — and focuses the gradient on hard examples. In Cityscapes, background vastly outnumbers objects, so this is a real concern.


For box regression we switch from Smooth L1 to GIoU loss. The key advantage of GIoU over Smooth L1 is that it's defined even when boxes don't overlap at all — it gives a gradient signal from the very start of training when the predicted box might be nowhere near the ground truth. Smooth L1 on raw coordinate deltas doesn't have that property.


The hypothesis: Focal Loss should help on rare classes — Train, Motorcycle, Rider — and GIoU should tighten the bounding boxes overall. The direct comparison to Exp 01 tells us exactly how much the loss function matters."


