Slide 20 — Summary

"To wrap up the object detection section.


We chose Faster R-CNN because Cityscapes specifically benefits from two-stage refinement — high resolution, small objects, heavy occlusion. Single-stage models make one shot; we wanted two.


We started from strong COCO pretrained weights, which already encode urban object features, and fine-tuned only the last layer due to hardware constraints.


Three experiments gave us a controlled comparison: Exp 01 is the baseline, Exp 02 tests whether better loss functions help, Exp 03 tests whether AdamW converges better than SGD.


The results show (your finding — whichever experiment won).


If we were to extend this work, the natural next steps are: increasing trainable layers to 2 or 3 if VRAM allows, adding data augmentation like horizontal flip and scale jitter which should give a few mAP points for free, and potentially looking at Cascade R-CNN which adds a third stage of refinement for dense scenes like this.


Happy to take questions."
